    "body": "I see `Exit message: Quit` of which second part comes I guess from https://github.com/ipython/ipython/commit/80515cc251c35cbde4a2bf331e4470fd213ed4fc#diff-e9a59ec7c6360d84aafa289edca1c50bR154 . I updated IPython and prompt-toolkit to lastest from github now, still the same happens. `Exit message: Quit` but echo is disabled in bash. That means Ctrl-\\ is handled by IPython as it should, but the cleanup is not done.\n\nStrange that you don't reproduce that. FWIW, I am on Ubuntu 16.04 with fairly standard env, running in libvte-based terminal emulator (terminator).\n"
